#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:0.5"
msgid "55. Bhiṃsāpanasikkhāpada"
msgstr ""
"<hgroup><h1 id=\"Bu-Pc.55\">Monks’ Confession 55: the training rule on "
"scaring</h1></hgroup>"

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"nidana\">Origin story</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.55.1\">Bu-Pc.55.1</a><a class=\"pts-vp-en\""
" id=\"BD.2.396\">BD.2.396</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1057</a>At one time the "
"Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū sattarasavaggiye bhikkhū "
"bhiṃsāpenti."
msgstr ""
"At that time the monks from the group of six were scaring the monks from the "
"group of seventeen."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:1.3"
msgid "Te bhiṃsāpīyamānā rodanti."
msgstr "They cried."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:1.4"
msgid "Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "Other monks asked them"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:1.5"
msgid "“kissa tumhe, āvuso, rodathā”ti?"
msgstr "why,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:1.6"
msgid "“Ime, āvuso, chabbaggiyā bhikkhū amhe bhiṃsāpentī”ti."
msgstr "and they told them.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:1.7"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1058</a>The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:1.8"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:1.9"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhuṃ bhiṃsāpessantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can the monks from the group of six scare other monks?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:1.10"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhuṃ bhiṃsāpethā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:1.11"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:1.12"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:1.13"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhuṃ bhiṃsāpessatha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you scare other monks?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:1.14"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:1.15"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="rule">
#. REF: sc3
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:1.16"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ bhiṃsāpeyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pannatti\">Final ruling</h2>\n"
"<p class=\"rule\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1059</a>‘If a monk scares another monk, "
"he commits an offense entailing confession.’”</p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc4
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pada\">Definitions</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.55.2\"></a><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-"
"Pc.55.2.1\">Bu-Pc.55.2.1</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1060</a><term>A</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "<gloss>whoever …</gloss>"

#. HTML: </b><b class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "<term>Monk</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"<gloss>…The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:2.1.6"
msgid "Bhikkhunti"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1061</a><term>Another monk</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:2.1.7"
msgid "aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ."
msgstr "<gloss>a different monk.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:2.1.8"
msgid "Bhiṃsāpeyyāti"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1062</a><term>Scares</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:2.1.9"
msgid ""
"upasampanno upasampannaṃ bhiṃsāpetukāmo rūpaṃ vā saddaṃ vā gandhaṃ vā rasaṃ "
"vā phoṭṭhabbaṃ vā upasaṃharati."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>if one who is fully ordained, wishing to scare another who is fully "
"ordained, arranges a sight, a sound, a smell, a taste, or a physical contact,"

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:2.1.10"
msgid "Bhāyeyya vā so na vā bhāyeyya, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"then whether the other monk is scared or not, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:2.1.11"
msgid "Corakantāraṃ vā vāḷakantāraṃ vā pisācakantāraṃ vā ācikkhati."
msgstr ""
"If he tells him about a wilderness inhabited by criminals, inhabited by wild "
"animals, or inhabited by demons,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:2.1.12"
msgid "Bhāyeyya vā so na vā bhāyeyya, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"then whether the other monk is scared or not, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:2.2.1"
msgid "Upasampanne upasampannasaññī bhiṃsāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"cakka\">Permutations</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.55.2.2\">Bu-Pc.55.2.2</a><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1063</a>If the other person is fully ordained, and he perceives him as "
"fully ordained, and he scares him, he commits an offense entailing "
"confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:2.2.2"
msgid "Upasampanne vematiko bhiṃsāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.397\">BD.2.397</a> If the other person is "
"fully ordained, but he is unsure if he is, and he scares him, he commits an "
"offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:2.2.3"
msgid "Upasampanne anupasampannasaññī bhiṃsāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If the other person is fully ordained, but he does not perceive him as fully "
"ordained, and he scares him, he commits an offense entailing confession.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8, pts-vp-pli4.115
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:2.2.4"
msgid ""
"Anupasampannaṃ bhiṃsāpetukāmo rūpaṃ vā saddaṃ vā gandhaṃ vā rasaṃ vā "
"phoṭṭhabbaṃ vā upasaṃharati."
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1064</a>If, wishing to scare someone who is not fully "
"ordained, he arranges a sight, a sound, a smell, a taste, or a physical "
"contact,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:2.2.5"
msgid "Bhāyeyya vā so na vā bhāyeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"then whether the other person is scared or not, he commits an offense of "
"wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:2.2.6"
msgid "Corakantāraṃ vā vāḷakantāraṃ vā pisācakantāraṃ vā ācikkhati."
msgstr ""
"If he tells him about a wilderness inhabited by criminals, inhabited by wild "
"animals, or inhabited by demons,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:2.2.7"
msgid "Bhāyeyya vā so na vā bhāyeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"then whether the other person is scared or not, he commits an offense of "
"wrong conduct.</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:2.2.8"
msgid "Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<p>If the other person is not fully ordained, but he perceives him as fully "
"ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:2.2.9"
msgid "Anupasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.115\">Vin.4.115</a> If the other person is "
"not fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong "
"conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:2.2.10"
msgid "Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If the other person is not fully ordained, and he does not perceive him as "
"fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"anapatti\">Non-offenses</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.55.2.3\">Bu-Pc.55.2.3</a><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1065</a>There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:2.3.2"
msgid ""
"na bhiṃsāpetukāmo rūpaṃ vā saddaṃ vā gandhaṃ vā rasaṃ vā phoṭṭhabbaṃ vā "
"upasaṃharati, corakantāraṃ vā vāḷakantāraṃ vā pisācakantāraṃ vā ācikkhati, "
"ummattakassa, ādikammikassāti."
msgstr ""
"if he arranges a sight, a sound, a smell, a taste, or a physical contact, or "
"he tells about a wilderness inhabited by criminals, inhabited by wild "
"animals, or inhabited by demons, but not because he wishes to scare anyone; "
"if he is insane; if he is the first offender.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc55:2.3.3"
msgid "Bhiṃsāpanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<hr><p class=\"endsutta\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1066</a>The fifth rule, the "
"training rule on scaring, is finished.</p>"
